.TH OMXREGISTER 1 "December 2007" Bellagio "OpenMAX Bellagio"
.SH NAME
omxregister \- register
.SM OpenMAX
components
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B omxregister [-v] [-h] [
.I componentspath
.B ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Before using any
.SM OpenMAX
component, they
.B must
be registered with the command
.B omxregister\.

That will create a registry file
.I .omxregistry
in the
.B $HOME
directory with all the components found by default in
.I @plugindir@
.SH OPTIONS
.IP -v
Display a verbose output, listing all the components registered.
.IP -h
Display help.
.SH FILES
.I $HOME/.omxregistry
.RS
The
.SM OpenMAX
component registry file.
.RE
.IP componentspath
Location of the
.SM OpenMAX
components (by default
.I @plugindir@
).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.IP HOME
.RS
Location of the home directory where registry is stored.
.RE
